Params: {1: '1', 2: 'Roland', 3: "Hey, are you sure this is the way? And why aren't you flying me there if you have wings...", 4: '1'}
{3: 'Roland slows down and sighs, complaining intentionally—he has to figure out a way to stall and get rid of the woman before him.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Voodoo', 3: "Fine by me. As long as you're not worried about falling from the sky and turning into a piece of junk.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Roland', 3: "Come on! I'm your comrade, am I not? Is that how you treat your comrades? How concerning...", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Voodoo?', 3: "Boy! You're not one of us! You stay around Mister because of your own agenda! We've never considered you as our comrade!", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Voodoo', 3: 'Why do you insist on finding that agent? She has lost all her power. She should be worth nothing to you.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 3: "Roland smiles. From Voodoo's inept probing, he is sure that this woman is here to keep an eye on him instead of accompanying him—her acting still has a long way to go."}

{2: 'Roland', 3: "Luna lost her power but not her status as an agent, which means Ascnet hasn't completely rejected her. If I can find her, perhaps I can find a way to obtain that status from her...", 4: '1'}
{3: 'And there it is: the perfect lie is always an ounce of falsehood enshrouded in truth. Now, he just needs to find out if Voodoo will be convinced.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Roland', 3: "Is it now? At least, I think it's a decent goal to aim for. Otherwise, there's no fun in staying alive…", 4: '1'}
{3: 'Voodoo suddenly stops, and Roland also pauses.'}
{1: '1', 3: 'Roland observes his surroundings quietly. Nothing is out of the ordinary—that said, there were plenty of opportunities on their way here for Voodoo to strike had she wanted.'}
{2: 'Roland', 3: 'Sigh... Finally. What a terrible journey that has been!', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Voodoo', 3: "We would've been here sooner had you not been complaining.", 4: '1'}
{3: 'Roland shrugs dramatically before following Voodoo into the ruins.'}
